review_text: Fitler Square, a charming neighborhood park in Philadelphia, is a half-acre haven of tranquility and natural beauty. Bounded by 23rd Street on the east, 24th Street on the west, Panama Street on the north, and Pine Street on the south, it‚Äôs a picturesque spot that offers a respite from the urban hustle. Named after the late 19th-century Philadelphia mayor Edwin Henry Fitler, the square is a testament to the city‚Äôs dedication to public spaces. With its well-maintained paths, seasonal flower beds, and a central fountain, Fitler Square is not just a park but a community gathering place that reflects the historic character of its surrounding neighborhood.
